<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">🤔 Why WebComponents?</h3>

<p class="mb-3 text-gray-500 mb-6">In an era of rapid technological changes and endless JavaScript framework hypes, I believe in the power of Web Standards 📜 that stand the test of time. WebComponents are like that timeless classic in your wardrobe that never goes out of style. They are designed to be compatible with the web's future improvements, making your development life smoother and more future-proof.</p>

<p class="mb-3 text-gray-500 mb-6">Also, there has been some movement behind this trend from big companies like Google (<a href="https://m3.material.io/" class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline hover:no-underline" target="_blank">Material</a> & <a href="https://lit.dev/" class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline hover:no-underline" target="_blank">Lit</a>), Microsoft (<a href="https://www.fast.design/" class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline hover:no-underline" target="_blank">Fast UI</a>), Ionic (<a href="https://stenciljs.com/" class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline hover:no-underline" target="_blank">Stencil</a>), Adobe (<a href="https://opensource.adobe.com/spectrum-web-components/" class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline hover:no-underline" target="_blank">Spectrum</a>), etc. who are pushing the standards to make it easier, more customizable and full of new interesting options! 👀</p>


